 hypothesis testing, and generalization of findings. They draw upon both the extensive body of qualitative analysis and the inchoate but important work of a quantitative nature. Although the chapters do not all focus specifically on the relationship between one state's nuclear behavior and that of another, collectively the essays provide a better understanding of the limits of reactive proliferation as well as the circumstances under which weapons diffusion is most likely to occur. They also offer compelling arguments about what must be done in order to improve proliferation prognoses and propose new conceptual approaches toward that end.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 4aPolitics -- International Relations. 4aSecurity Studies -- Global Security. 4aSecurity Studies -- Proliferation and WMD. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / Arms Control.2bisacsh1 aBajema, Natasha E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBleek, Philipp C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDunn, Lewis A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHymans, Jacques E. C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMukhatzhanova, Gaukhar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMukhatzhanova, Gaukhar, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMüller, Harald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPotter, William C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPotter, William, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSagan, Scott D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchmidt, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSolingen, Etel, eco